The paper focuses on privacy-enhancing aggregation of distributed sensor data, which falls under the category of security and privacy (cs.CR). The use of real-time data analytics and aggregate information also suggests a possible connection to information retrieval (cs.IR) and database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the management and regulation of smart city infrastructures, which could be related to social and information networks (cs.SI) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
